{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":1491,"record_hash":"sha256:1aef0ca122f6d0dca89f18652c4f55e1faffc17ee6ecb53f4e863a2354f913a1","timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:24:08.593Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 3770c7\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 867\nOutput:\n---\nname: but-agentlog\nversion: 0.0.0\ndescription: \"Recover agent handoff context from GitButler agentlog captures. Use when finding related agent sessions for a branch, review, or change; inspecting session timelines; hydrating bounded records; or summarizing prior agent work from `but agentlog`.\"\nauthor: GitButler Team\n---\n\n# GitButler Agentlog Skill\n\nUse `but agentlog` to recover prior agent work from captured sessions.\n\n## Core Workflow\n\nUse the commands as a narrowing funnel:\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog sessions branch <branch-name-or-ref> --limit 5\nbut agentlog sessions review <review-id-or-key> --limit 5\nbut agentlog sessions change <change-id-or-key> --limit 5\n\nbut agentlog timeline <session-key> --limit 20\nbut agentlog records <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n```\n\n1. Start with `sessions` for the branch, review, or change.\n2. Choose the freshest relevant `session_key`.\n3. Inspect `timeline` for turn-level context.\n4. Hydrate `records` only for turns that need exact detail.\n\n## Rules\n\n- Prefer orientation before payload.\n- Do not dump records for every candidate session.\n- Treat matches as related evidence, not ownership.\n- Cite `session_key`, relevant `turn_key`s, and the target used for discovery.\n- Use record snippets only when they justify the next action.\n- Say \"session related to branch X via turn Y\", not \"session for branch X\".\n\n## Reading `sessions`\n\nUse `sessions` to answer which captured sessions are probably relevant.\n\nUseful fields:\n\n- `session_key`: handle for follow-up reads.\n- `latest_captured_at`: freshness signal.\n- `record_count` and `turn_count`: size estimate before hydration.\n- `related_turn_keys`: direct target evidence.\n- `match_evidence`: why the session was returned.\n- `observed_targets`: branch/review/change keys observed in related turns.\n- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: quick intent/result scan.\n\nRelated sessions are sorted by latest activity.\n\n## Reading `timeline`\n\nUse `timeline` to answer what happened in a session at turn granularity.\n\nUseful fields:\n\n- `coverage`: returned turns versus total turns.\n- `turn_key`: handle for `records`.\n- `turn_index`: order within the session.\n- `capture_kind`: backfill or incremental.\n- `record_count`: turn size before hydrating records.\n- `source_record_index_range`: provider/source indexes covered by the turn.\n- `observed_targets`: targets observed in the turn.\n- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: compact orientation.\n- `tool_counts`: tool call/result counts and tool names.\n\nIncrease `--limit` only when the current window misses the related turn or setup.\n\n## Reading `records`\n\nUse `records` to answer what exactly happened inside one turn.\n\nUseful fields:\n\n- `coverage`: returned records versus total records in the turn.\n- `turn_record_index`: order within the turn.\n- `source_record_index`: original provider/source index when available.\n- `timestamp`, `kind`, `role`, `text`: message/tool orientation.\n- `tool_name` and `tool_input`: tool details when present.\n- `source_record`: redacted stored provider envelope for low-level debugging.\n\n`records` is intentionally bounded. Increase `--limit` only for a specific turn\nafter `timeline` shows that more detail is needed.\n\n## Handoff Summary\n\nWhen summarizing recovered context, include:\n\n- target used for discovery\n- chosen `session_key`\n- relevant `turn_key`s\n- previews explaining intent and outcome\n- minimal record snippets for the next action\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T03:24:08.593Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}